<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Dudleya</i> <i>greenei</i> or other rare Dudleya is the dominant herb. Other herbs include <i>Astragalus</i> <i>miguelensis</i>, <i>Carpobrotus</i> <i>chilensis</i>, <i>Erigeron</i> <i>glaucus</i>, <i>Extriplex</i> <i>californica</i> or <i>Mesembryanthemum</i> <i>crystallinum</i>. Commonly associated emergent shrubs at sparse cover include <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>grande</i>, <i>Isocoma</i> <i>menziesii</i> and <i>Leptosyne</i> <i>gigantea</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  The shrub layer is sparse to open.  The herbaceous layer is open to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Dudleya </i>spp. > 50% relative cover in an open to intermittent herbaceous layer (Rodriguez et al. 2017).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Coastal bluffs and terraces, including on steep rock outcrops and flats.  </div>
</div>

        
